HEADWORD: Southron
<hw>South"ron</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An inhabitant of the
more southern part of a country; formerly, a name given in Scotland to
any Englishman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

